rror type, and the error payload contains all three attempts each paired with their respective test failure output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.63,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.09,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full loop — generate, test, refine, test again — produces a working implementation for a function that a single LLM call typically gets wrong.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MULTI-STEP: 'Generate, test, refine, test again' is explicitly a multi-step agentic pipeline; the behavior cannot be exercised with a single LLM call. LLM-DEP: 'A single LLM call typically gets wrong' directly asserts that the value is in the feedback loop improving real LLM output across attempts — a stub always returns what we program it to, hiding whether the real iterative refinement mechanism actually works. REAL-INFRA: Running generated code against real test cases requires real code execution; an in-process fake would mask runtime errors in generated implementations. REJECTION-GATE: The behavior explicitly calls out the multi-step loop and the fact that single-call generation fails — no text disqualifies Workflow in favor of Agentic.","test_description":"Run the full service against the real LLM using a canonical function known to fail on the first attempt (e.g., one requiring careful handling of an edge case like empty input or integer overflow). Assert that at least one intermediate attempt fails its tests, that each subsequent prompt contains the prior failure messages, and that the final attempt produces a passing implementation.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.78}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10012,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m